=========================================================
INTERVIEW READY ANSWER (30 Seconds)
=========================================================

RAII stands for Resource Acquisition Is Initialization. The idea is to
acquire resources such as memory, files, mutexes, or sockets in a
constructor and release them in the destructor. Since C++ guarantees
automatic destructor calls during scope exit and exception handling,
RAII provides automatic resource management, exception safety, and helps
prevent memory and resource leaks. Smart pointers and lock_guard are
classic examples of RAII.

